  65      """C{Table} is used for representing data or components in a 
  66      pageable and selectable table. 
  67   
  68      Scalability of the Table is largely dictated by the container. A table 
  69      does not have a limit for the number of items and is just as fast with 
  70      hundreds of thousands of items as with just a few. The current GWT 
  71      implementation with scrolling however limits the number of rows to 
  72      around 500000, depending on the browser and the pixel height of rows. 
  73   
  74      Components in a Table will not have their caption nor icon rendered. 
  75   
  76      @author: Vaadin Ltd. 
  77      @author: Richard Lincoln 
  78      @version: 1.1.0
